The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC, has denied media report that its operatives arrested immediate past governor of Imo state, Rochas Okorocha. It was earlier reported that Okorocha and his wife were arrested by EFCC agents. When contacted on Thursday the acting spokesman of the Commission Tony Orilade said the report is not only false but fake news.   Oshiomhole should resign from APC - Nwafor I’m a success story in Imo – Okorocha Okorocha secures NUC recognition for 3 new universities in Imo Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin